<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/2127⅓</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the Under Secretary of State</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-01">May 1,
                                    1940</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I am glad Mr. Van Zeeland is making progress and I think the best
                                thing would be for me to send a personal request to Mr. Baruch that
                                he meet with Mr. Van Zeeland and possibly with Mr. Rosenwald and Mr.
                                Ittleson—preferably in New York. I will tell Mr. Baruch, however,
                                that the general plan has my full approval.</p>
                            <p>Will you let me know what you think?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>